The paper deals with the construction of sparse matrices from expander graphs, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves asymptotic analysis and quantitative sampling theorems, which are related to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of these matrices for linear sketching, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG).
